Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of medical image classification using limited amounts of labelled data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves using semi-supervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach also involves using deep neural networks (cs.DL) and hybrid models, which combine model-based functional and deep net approaches. Finally, the paper involves extensive numerical comparisons, which suggests a focus on optimization and neural networks (cs.NE).
